\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces SDs for thermal noise ($\text  {R}=987\pm 5\Omega $, $T=295.3\pm 0.1$K). The data (grey), the reduced band of analysis (blue), and the average across the reduced band (black) are plotted against the theoretical value (red) of $1.610\pm 0.09\cdot 10^{-17}$ V$^2$/Hz. (a) Raw PSD. (b) Gain adjusted (GA) PSD: average value $3.00\pm 0.09\cdot 10^{-17}$ V$^2$/Hz; percent difference $86.1$\% (c) GA CSD (see Table \ref {tab:CSDavg} for results).}}{3}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:CSD}{{3}{3}{SDs for thermal noise ($\text {R}=987\pm 5\Omega $, $T=295.3\pm 0.1$K). The data (grey), the reduced band of analysis (blue), and the average across the reduced band (black) are plotted against the theoretical value (red) of $1.610\pm 0.09\cdot 10^{-17}$ V$^2$/Hz. (a) Raw PSD. (b) Gain adjusted (GA) PSD: average value $3.00\pm 0.09\cdot 10^{-17}$ V$^2$/Hz; percent difference $86.1$\% (c) GA CSD (see Table \ref {tab:CSDavg} for results)}{figure.3}{}}
