\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces (a) Linear fitting of PSD (black), CSD (blue), and theoretic thermal noise (red) as a function of resistance. PSD: (slope: $(1.70\pm 0.03)\cdot 10^{-20}$V$^2$/(Hz$\Omega $), reduced $\chi ^2$: $0.07$). CSD: (slope: $(1.69\pm 0.03)\cdot 10^{-20}$V$^2$/(Hz$\Omega $), reduced $\chi ^2$: $0.05$). Theory: (slope: $1.63\cdot 10^{-20}$V$^2$/(Hz$\Omega $)) (b) Residuals of experimental data versus theoretic expectations for the PSD (black) and CSD (blue), with theory as the base line(red).}}{4}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:JNvR}{{4}{4}{(a) Linear fitting of PSD (black), CSD (blue), and theoretic thermal noise (red) as a function of resistance. PSD: (slope: $(1.70\pm 0.03)\cdot 10^{-20}$V$^2$/(Hz$\Omega $), reduced $\chi ^2$: $0.07$). CSD: (slope: $(1.69\pm 0.03)\cdot 10^{-20}$V$^2$/(Hz$\Omega $), reduced $\chi ^2$: $0.05$). Theory: (slope: $1.63\cdot 10^{-20}$V$^2$/(Hz$\Omega $)) (b) Residuals of experimental data versus theoretic expectations for the PSD (black) and CSD (blue), with theory as the base line(red)}{figure.4}{}}
